Author-Name:  George W. Evans
Author-Name:  Seppo Honkapohja 
Title: Expectations and the Stability Problem for Optimal Monetary Policies 
Abstract:
 A fundamentals based monetary policy rule, which would be the optimal
 monetary policy without commitment when private agents have perfectly
 rational expectations, is unstable if in fact these agents follow standard
 adaptive learning rules. This problem can be overcome if private
 expectations are observed and suitably incorporated into the policy
 maker's optimal rule. These strong results extend to the case in which
 there is simultaneous learning by the policy maker and the private agents.
 Our findings show the importance of conditioning policy appropriately, not
 just on fundamentals, but also directly on observed household and firm
 expectations.  Copyright 2003, Wiley-Blackwell.
