Title: Precautionary Wealth Accumulation 
Abstract:
 When does an individual's expected wealth accumulation profile increase as
 earnings risk increases? This paper answers this question for multi-period
 models where earnings shocks are independent over time. Sufficient
 conditions are stated in terms of properties of a decision rule for
 savings and, alternatively, in terms of properties of preferences.  Copyright 2004, Wiley-Blackwell.
