Author-Name:  Ignacio Palacios-Huerta
Title: Professionals Play Minimax 
Abstract:
 The implications of the Minimax theorem are tested using natural data. The
 tests use a unique data set from penalty kicks in professional soccer
 games. In this natural setting experts play a one-shot two-person zero-sum
 game. The results of the tests are remarkably consistent with equilibrium
 play in every respect: (i) winning probabilities are statistically
 identical across strategies for players; (ii) players' choices are
 serially independent. The tests have substantial power to distinguish
 equilibrium play from disequilibrium alternatives. These results represent
 the first time that both implications of von Neumann's Minimax theorem are
 supported under natural conditions.  Copyright 2003, Wiley-Blackwell.
