Author-Name:  Jean Tirole 
Title: Bubbly Liquidity 
Abstract:
 This paper analyses the possibility and the consequences of rational
 bubbles in a dynamic economy where financially constrained firms demand
 and supply liquidity. Bubbles are more likely to emerge, the scarcer the
 supply of outside liquidity and the more limited the pledgeability of
 corporate income; they crowd investment in (out) when liquidity is
 abundant (scarce). We analyse extensions with firm heterogeneity and
 stochastic bubbles.  Copyright 2012, Oxford University Press.
