Title: Informational Size and Efficient Auctions 
Abstract:
 We develop an auction model for the case of interdependent values and
 multidimensional signals in which agents' signals are correlated. We
 provide conditions under which a modification of the Vickrey auction which
 includes payments to the bidders will result in an ex post efficient
 outcome. Furthermore, we provide a definition of informational size such
 that the necessary payments to bidders will be arbitrarily small if agents
 are sufficiently informationally small.  Copyright 2004, Wiley-Blackwell.
