Author-Name:  Jayant V. Ganguli 
Title: Ambiguity and Rational Expectations Equilibria 
Abstract:
 This paper demonstrates the existence and robustness of partially
 revealing rational expectations equilibria in general exchange economies
 when some traders have non-smooth ambiguity-averse preferences. This
 finding illustrates that models with non-smooth ambiguity aversion provide
 a relatively tractable framework through which partial information
 revelation may be studied in a general equilibrium setting without relying
 on particular distributional or von Neumann--Morgenstern utility
 assumptions or the presence of "noise."  Copyright 2011, Oxford University Press.
