Author-Name:  Luis Rayo
Title: Relational Incentives and Moral Hazard in Teams 
Abstract:
 This paper studies moral hazard in teams using a model where efforts are
 promoted via the combination of profit shares and relational contracts.
 The focus is on how these two forms of incentives interact. According to
 the degree of effort observability and the importance of future
 interaction, the optimal allocation of profit shares can range from a wide
 dispersion across players to a full concentration of shares in the hands
 of a single player. When shares are sufficiently concentrated, the
 corresponding residual claimant can also adopt the role of administering
 all relational contracts, therefore serving as an endogenously chosen
 principal.  Copyright 2007, Wiley-Blackwell.
