Author-Name:  Ran Spiegler
Title: Equilibrium in Justifiable Strategies: A Model of Reason-based Choice in Extensive-form Games 
Abstract:
 I explore the idea that people care about the justifiability of their
 decisions in the context of two-person extensive games. Each player
 justifies his strategy s with a belief b of the opponent's strategy which
 is consistent with the play path and maximally plausible (according to
 some exogenous criterion). We say that s is justifiable if against the ex
 post criticism that some other strategy s&#x2032; outperforms s against b,
 the player can argue that playing s&#x2032; would have exposed him to
 similar criticism in the opposite direction. Under a simplicity-based
 plausibility criterion, this concept implies systematic departures from
 maximizing behaviour in familiar games.  Copyright 2002, Wiley-Blackwell.
