Title: Empirical Analysis of Limit Order Markets 
Abstract:
 We provide empirical restrictions of a model of optimal order submissions
 in a limit order market. A trader's optimal order submission depends on
 the trader's valuation for the asset and the trade-offs between order
 prices, execution probabilities and picking off risks. The optimal order
 submission strategy is a monotone function of a trader's valuation for the
 asset. We test the monotonicity restriction in a sample of order
 submissions and their realized outcomes from the Stockholm Stock Exchange.
 We do not reject the monotonicity restriction for buy orders or sell
 orders considered separately, but reject the monotonicity restriction for
 buy and sell orders considered jointly.  Copyright 2004, Wiley-Blackwell.
