Title: Efficient Estimation of the Parameter Path in Unstable Time Series Models 
Abstract:
 The paper investigates inference in non-linear and non-Gaussian models
 with moderately time-varying parameters. We show that for many decision
 problems, the sample information about the parameter path can be
 summarized by an artificial linear and Gaussian model, at least
 asymptotically. The approximation allows for computationally convenient
 path estimators and parameter stability tests. Also, in contrast to
 standard Bayesian techniques, the artificial model can be robustified so
 that in misspecified models, decisions about the path of the (pseudo-true)
 parameter remain as good as in a corresponding correctly specified model.  Copyright , Wiley-Blackwell.
