Author-Name:  Boyan Jovanovic
Title: Asymmetric Cycles 
Abstract:
 I estimate a model in which new technology entails random adjustment
 needs. Rapid adjustments may cause measured productivity to decline. The
 slow-downs persist because adjustment is costly, and hence protracted. The
 model explains both the &#x201C;steepness&#x201D; and the
 &#x201C;deepness&#x201D; asymmetry of cycles. Adjustment costs amount to
 about 14&#x0025; of output and technological inefficiency to about
 28&#x0025;. Firms abandon technologies long before they are
 perfected&#x2014;current practice total factor productivity (TFP) is
 20&#x0025; below its maximal level.  Copyright 2006, Wiley-Blackwell.
