 journal, <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="R1">2000</xref>), Barlevy and Veronesi
 present a model of a one-period financial market, and claim that for an
 open set of parameter values, the value of information increases with the
 mass of informed agents. That claim is shown here to be false. The
