Title: Assigning Resources to Budget-Constrained Agents 
Abstract:
 This article studies different methods of assigning a good to
 budget-constrained agents. Schemes that assign the good randomly and allow
 resale may outperform the competitive market in terms of Utilitarian
 efficiency. The socially optimal mechanism involves random assignment at a
 discount--an in-kind subsidy--and a cash incentive to discourage
 low-valuation individuals from claiming the good.  Copyright , Oxford University Press.
