Title: An Axiomatic Model of Non-Bayesian Updating 
Abstract:
 This paper models an agent in a three-period setting who does not update
 according to Bayes' Rule and who is self-aware and anticipates her
 updating behaviour when formulating plans. Gul and Pesendorfer's theory of
 temptation and self-control is a key building block. The main result is a
 representation theorem that generalizes (the dynamic version of)
 Anscombe-Aumann's theorem so that both the prior and the way in which it
 is updated are subjective. The model can accommodate updating biases
 analogous to those observed by psychologists.  Copyright 2006, Wiley-Blackwell.
