Author-Name:  David McAdams 
Title: Monotone Equilibrium in Multi-Unit Auctions 
Abstract:
 In two-sided multi-unit auctions having a variety of payment rules,
 including uniform-price and discriminatory auctions, a monotone
 pure-strategy equilibrium (MPSE) exists when bidders are risk neutral with
 independent multi-dimensional types and interdependent values. In fact,
 all mixed-strategy equilibria are ex post allocation and interim expected
 payment equivalent to MPSE. Thus, for standard expected surplus/revenue
 analysis, there is no loss restricting attention to monotone strategies.  Copyright 2006, Wiley-Blackwell.
