Title: Valid Inference in Partially Unstable Generalized Method of Moments Models 
Abstract:
 This paper considers time series Generalized Method of Moments (GMM)
 models where a subset of the parameters are time varying. We focus on an
 empirically relevant case with moderately large instabilities, which are
 well approximated by a local asymptotic embedding that does not allow the
 instability to be detected with certainty, even in the limit. We show that
 for many forms of the instability and a large class of GMM models, usual
 GMM inference on the subset of stable parameters is asymptotically
 unaffected by the partial instability. In the empirical analysis of
 presumably stable parameters&#x02014;such as structural parameters in
 Euler conditions&#x02014;one can thus ignore moderate instabilities in
 other parts of the model and still obtain approximately correct inference.  Copyright , Wiley-Blackwell.
