Title: Non-linear Capital Taxation Without Commitment 
Abstract:
 We study efficient non-linear taxation of labour and capital in a dynamic
 Mirrleesian model incorporating political economy constraints. Policies
 are chosen sequentially over time, without commitment. Our main result is
 that the marginal tax on capital income is progressive, in the sense that
 richer agents face higher marginal tax rates.  Copyright , Oxford University Press.
