Title: Compensating Variation and Hicksian Choice Probabilities in Random Utility Models that are Nonlinear in Income 
Abstract:
 In this paper we discuss Hicksian demand and compensating variation in the
 context of discrete choice. We first derive Hicksian choice probabilities
 and the distribution of the (random) expenditure function in the general
 case when the utilities are nonlinear in income. We subsequently derive
 exact and simple formulae for the expenditure and choice probabilities
 under price (policy) changes conditional on the initial utility level.
 This is of particular interest for welfare measurement because it enables
 the researcher to compute the distribution of compensating variation in a
 simple way. We also derive formulae for the joint distribution of
 expenditure, the choice before and after a policy change has been
 introduced.  Copyright 2005, Wiley-Blackwell.
