Author-Name:  Fabrizio Mattesini 
Author-Name:  Randall Wright 
Title: Banking: A New Monetarist Approach 
Abstract:
 We develop a model where: (i) banks take deposits and make investments;
 (ii) their liabilities facilitate third-party transactions. Other models
 have (i) or (ii), not both, although we argue they are intimately
 connected: we show that they both emerge from limited commitment. We
 describe an environment, characterize desirable allocations, and interpret
 the outcomes as banking arrangements. Banks are essential: without them,
 the set of feasible allocations is inferior. As a technical contribution,
 we characterize dynamically optimal credit allocations with frictions,
 show they involve backloading, and analyse how this interacts with
 banking. We also confront the theory with economic history.  Copyright 2013, Oxford University Press.
