Author-Name:  John V. Leahy
Author-Name:  Joseph Zeira 
Title: The Timing of Purchases and Aggregate Fluctuations 
Abstract:
 We study the cyclical effects of the timing of durable goods purchases in
 a general equilibrium model in which both durable and non-durable goods
 are consumed and the durable good is lumpy. At the microeconomic level,
 the timing of durable goods purchases supplies some insulation for
 nondurable consumption over the cycle. At the macroeconomic level, the
 timing decisions tend to amplify and propagate wealth and income shocks.
 Our model also allows for endogenous price determination. When the price
 of the durable changes due to inflexibility of workers between sectors,
 the effect of adverse shocks is even stronger and longer.  Copyright 2005, Wiley-Blackwell.
