Title: Poverty and Witch Killing 
Abstract:
 This study uses rainfall variation to estimate the impact of income shocks
 on murder in rural Tanzania. Extreme rainfall (drought or flood) leads to
 a large increase in the murder of "witches"&#x02014;typically elderly
 women killed by relatives&#x02014;but not other murders. The findings
 provide novel evidence on the role of income shocks in causing violent
 crime, and religious violence in particular.  Copyright 2005, Wiley-Blackwell.
