Author-Name:  Vincent Feltkamp 
Title: A Bayesian Approach to Uncertainty Aversion 
Abstract:
 The Ellsberg paradox demonstrates that people's beliefs over uncertain
 events might not be representable by subjective probability. We show that
 if a risk averse decision maker, who has a well defined Bayesian prior,
 perceives an Ellsberg type decision problem as possibly composed of a
 bundle of several positively correlated problems, she will be uncertainty
 averse. We generalize this argument and derive sufficient conditions for
 uncertainty aversion.  Copyright 2005, Wiley-Blackwell.
