Author-Name:  Ariel Rubinstein 
Author-Name:  Yuval Salant 
Title: Eliciting Welfare Preferences from Behavioural Data Sets 
Abstract:
 An individual displays various preference orderings in different
 payoff-irrelevant circumstances. It is assumed that the variation in the
 observed preference orderings is the outcome of some cognitive process
 that distorts the underlying preferences of the individual. We introduce a
 framework for eliciting the individual's underlying preferences in such
 cases and then demonstrate it for two cognitive processes--satisficing and
 small assessment errors.  Copyright 2012, Oxford University Press.
