Author-Name:  Patrick Bolton
Author-Name:  Antoine Faure-Grimaud 
Title: Thinking Ahead: The Decision Problem 
Abstract:
 We propose a model of costly decision making based on time-costs of
 deliberating current and future decisions. We model an individual
 decision-maker's thinking process as a thought-experiment that takes time,
 and lets the decision maker 'think ahead' about future decision problems
 in yet unrealized states of nature. By formulating an intertemporal,
 state-contingent, planning problem which may involve costly deliberation
 in every state of nature, and by letting the decision maker deliberate
 ahead of the realization of a state, we attempt to capture the basic
 observation that individuals generally do not think through a complete
 action plan. Instead, individuals prioritize their thinking and leave
 deliberations on less important decisions to the time or event when they
 arise.  Copyright 2009, Wiley-Blackwell.
