Title: Escaping Nash Inflation 
Abstract:
 An ordinary differential equation (ODE) gives the mean dynamics that
 govern the convergence to self-confirming equilibria of self-referential
 systems under discounted least squares learning. Another ODE governs
 escape dynamics that recurrently propel away from a selfconfirming
 equilibrium. In a model with a unique self-confirming equilibrium, the
 escape dynamics make the government discover too strong a version of the
 natural rate hypothesis. The escape route dynamics cause recurrent
 outcomes close to the Ramsey (commitment) inflation rate in a model with
 an adaptive government.&#x201C;If an unlikely event occurs, it is very
 likely to occur in the most likly way.&#x201D;Michael Harrison  Copyright 2002, Wiley-Blackwell.
